  <reg:title>Stl'atl'imx Tribal Police Service Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e25" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Geographical area</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The geographical area within which the designated policing unit and its designated constables for the Stl'atl'imx Tribal Police Service must operate is set out in the attached Schedule.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e37">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Powers, duties and functions of the board of the Stl'atl'imx Tribal Police Service</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The powers, duties and functions of the board of the Stl'atl'imx Tribal Police Service include those set out in section 4.2 (2) (c) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96367_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Police Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:schedule>
